{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_9","type":"agent_message","text":"The repo already has an audio stage skeleton, intent contracts, and job records, so the right move is to extend the durable session snapshot and existing stage editor patterns instead of adding a separate audio subsystem.\n\nPlan:\n1. Trace the current audio-related backend models, repositories, and route handlers to find the durable write path for stage edits and chat echoes.\n2. Extend the session/audio data model with structured preferences, add migration and service/repository support, and keep compatibility with existing audio job fields.\n3. Build the audio settings stage UI around those durable fields, wire save/update behavior through the existing workspace mutation flow, and surface concise action-history/chat summaries.\n4. Verify with targeted backend and frontend tests, then run browser-based visual QA against the Docker Compose app on desktop and mobile.\n5. Commit coherent checkpoints, then write the required reviewer summary file as the final step."}}
